==Norwegian==
===Adverb===
'''av'''
# [[off#Adjective|off]]; not operating.
#: ''å sla av'' (to turn off).
# [[from]].
#: ''fra barn av'' (from childhood)
# [[of]].
#: ''bli av med'' (get rid of)
# [[now]].
#: ''[[av og til]]'' ([[now and then]])

===Preposition===
'''av'''
# [[from]].
# [[by]] (in construction of the passive tense).
#: ''Huset ble malt av ham'' (The house was painted by him).
# [[of]].
# [[for]].
# [[in]], [[out of]].
# [[on]]
#: ''Avhenging av'' (Dependant on).

==Swedish==
{{see|av-}}
===Preposition===
'''av'''
# [[from]].
# [[by]] (in construction of the passive tense).
#: ''The house was painted by him'' = ''Huset målades av honom''
# [[of]].
# [[abbreviation]] of [[avstängd]] ([[shut down]]).
# [[broken]].

====Derived terms====
*[[lasta av]]
*:unload (concerning transportations)
*[[stänga av]]
